>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Frost Giants</span><hr size=1> after i levelled quite fast after 44, i want to share my experiences with follow mages (btw 43 was hell for me then 45!)<br>
<br>
if you go for Kael faction, you should not do the following things, but it is good for thurgadin and skyshire faction.<br>
<br>
basically i hunted Frost Giant (FG) scouts and 'normal' ones. when i got close to 48, i could solo the 'berserkers' in Great Divide, which reminds me, even if some have the same name, their levels vary very much depending on zone !<br>
<br>
start in Great Divide ... i preferred a spot close to East Wastes zone (when you head from Thurgadin towards East Wastes, it is on the left, near a tree at the wall ... you can't miss that!). starting at 44 most 'scouts' will be easy, but get yourself SoW potions or JBoots as early as possible ... it will safe you some deaths and the money for rezzes. don't try 'berserkers' without SoW !<br>
<br>
[if you are going to group there, only take lowers level in your group !]<br>
<br>
these FGs drop money in the 1pp to 6pp range and sometimes drop quite some nice items (i got 1 'Drakkel Icegrinder' and 1 'Drakkel Icereaver' off them !). also they drop 'heads', 'toes' and 'helmets'.<br>
<br>
collect them all !!! 1st they are for the 'Thurgadin Shawl' quest (you need 4 toes for the 1st part, and 10 heads for the 2nd part), that results in a not to bad item.<br>
<br>
after you did the shawl quest, use the 'heads' to trade in for 'toes' and 'helmets' as they are useful for a small quest in 'Skyshire' to improve BOTH factions there. killing FGs 'only' gives you 'ClawsofVeshaan' (maybe wrong spelling) faction, but this other quest also gives you 'Yelinic' (oh damned, this must be pretty wrong spelling). the dragon at the circle in 'Wakening Lands' has 'ClawsofVeshaan' faction (her name is Woushi) ... and is somewhat better to have faction with her ... ;-)<br>
<br>
for the 'helmets' and 'toes' quest in 'Skyshire': there are two guards at the first gate inside the zone ... just give them your 'trophies' and get the factions ('toes' also give you some money). some say, 'toes' don't always work. hmmm, i always used the left guard (looking towards the gate) and he always gave me faction for 'toes'.<br>
<br>
if 'scouts' and 'berserkers' in 'Great Divide' get boring, try the 'normal' ones, _close_ to the FG fort in 'Eastern Wastes' or any others you can find ... ;-) ... they are somewhat harder, and killed me from time to time in the 45/46 range. also watch out for 'Snow Griffs' and 'Manticores'. <br>
<br>
At some point you need 'Snow Griffs' for the 3rd part of the shawl quest. I hunted them at end 46 to mid 47 ... for a change.<br>
<br>
if you need a change in colors: go to wakening lands and hunt those raptors. there is a spawn close to skyshire (just to the left, when you leave skyshire). they are easy and give good exp ... but almost no loot at all ... but i couldn't see white anymore ... and wakening lands is quite a change in color.<br>
<br>
if you can't or don't want to see FGs anymore, try griffs, orcs, kodiaks, and other things in 'Easter Wastes' ... but don't try to solo 'Manticores' ... well, try them for a death experience ... i know, it is always hard to believe, if you haven't felt it .. ;-)<br>
<br>
as i write this, i sit down here in 'Lake of Ill Omen' doing 'Bloodgill Goblins' and get sort fo frustrated of them ... i start to miss my FGs ... better spawn rate, more changes to get killed, IMHO better loot. also GD or EW aren't that crowded, like LOIO, or DL.<br>
<br>
maybe i will add some more infos about 48 in the future ... ;-)<br>
<br>
  - bilt<br>
